# Godot presubmit (warnings as errors)

`Hafnium/project.godot` sets `[debug] gdscript/warnings/` so some warnings (e.g. `untyped_declaration`, `inferred_declaration` at level **2**) are **errors**, matching the editor and debug adapter—**not** identical to `gdlint` alone.

After substantive edits to `Hafnium/**/*.gd`, before finishing the task run **one** of:

| Environment | Command (from repo root) |
|-------------|--------------------------|
| Bash / Git Bash | `bash Hafnium/presubmit_godot_compile.sh` |
| PowerShell | `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File Hafnium/presubmit_godot_compile.ps1` |

Requires Godot on `PATH` or `GODOT_BIN` pointing at the Godot executable.

Also run `gdlint` on touched files when `gdtoolkit` is installed (`pip install gdtoolkit`), as in the repo pre-commit hook.

Do not introduce implicit types (`:=` without an explicit annotation where the project would error), or untyped declarations where level-2 warnings apply.
